                "paragraphs": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "sentences": [
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Second language (L2) learning requires the ac- quisition of vocabulary as well as knowledge of the language\u2019s constructions."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "One of the ways in which learners become familiar with novel vocab- ulary and constructions is through reading."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Ac- cording to Krashen\u2019s Input Hypothesis (Krashen, 1989), learners acquire language through inciden- tal learning, which occurs when learners are ex- posed to comprehensible input."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "What constitutes \u201ccomprehensible input\u201d for a learner varies as their knowledge of the L2 increases."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "For example, a student in their first month of German lessons would be hard-pressed to read German novels or even front-page news, but they might understand brief descriptions of daily routines."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Comprehen- sible input need not be completely familiar to the learner; it could include novel vocabulary items or structures (whose meanings they can glean from context)."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Such input falls in the \u201czone of proxi- maldevelopment\u201d(Vygotski \u0306\u0131,2012),justoutside of the learner\u2019s comfort zone."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "The related concept of \u201cscaffolding\u201d (Wood et al., 1976) consists of providing assistance to the learner at a level that is just sufficient for them to complete their task, which in our case is understanding a sentence."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "sentences": [
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Automatic selection or construction of comprehensible input\u2014perhaps online and personalized\u2014would be a useful educational technology."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "However, this requires modeling the student: what can an L2 learner understand in a given context?"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "In this paper, we develop a model and train its parameters on data that we collect."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "sentences": [
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "For the remainder of the paper we focus on native English speakers learning German."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Our methodology is a novel solution to the problem of controlling for the learner\u2019s German skill level."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "We use subjects with zero previous knowledge of German, but we translate portions of the sentence into English."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Thus, we can presume that they do already know the English words and do not al- ready know the German words (except from see- ing them in earlier trials within our experiment)."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "We are interested in whether they can jointly infer the meanings of the remaining German words in the sentence, so we ask them to guess."
                            }
                        ]
