            {
                "type": "section",
                "title": "3 Data Collection Setup",
                "paragraphs": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "sentences": [
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Our method of scaffolding is to replace certain for- eign words and phrases with their English trans- lations, yielding a macaronic sentence.1 Simply presenting these to a learner would not give us feedback on the learner\u2019s belief state for each for- eign word."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Even assessing the learner\u2019s reading comprehension would give only weak indirect in- formation about what was understood."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Thus, we collect data where a learner explicitly guesses a foreign word\u2019s translation when seen in the mac- aronic context."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "These guesses are then treated as supervised labels to train our user model."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "sentences": [
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "We used Amazon Mechanical Turk (MTurk) to collect data."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Users qualified for tasks by completing a short quiz and survey about their language knowledge."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Only users whose results indicated no knowledge of German and self-identified as native speakers of English were allowed to complete tasks."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "With German as the foreign language, we generated content by crawling a simplified German news website, nachrichtenleicht."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "de."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "We chose simplified German in order to minimize translation errors and to make the task more suitable for novice learners."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "We translated each German sentence using the Moses Statistical Machine Translation (SMT) toolkit (Koehn et al., 2007)."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "The SMT system was trained on the German-English Commoncrawl parallel text used in WMT 2015 (Bojar et al., 2015)."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "sentences": [
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "We used 200 German sentences, presenting each to 10 different users."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "In MTurk jargon, this yielded 2000 Human Intelligence Tasks (HITs)."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "Each HIT required its user to participate in several rounds of guessing as the English translation was incrementally revealed."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "A user was paid US$0.12 per HIT, with a bonus of US$6 to any user who accumulated more than 2000 total points."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "sentences": [
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "3.1 HITs and Submissions, For each HIT, the user first sees a German sen- tence2 (Figure 1)."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "A text box is presented below each German word in the sentence, for the userto type in their \u201cbest guess\u201d of what each Ger- man word means."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "The user must fill in at least half of the text boxes before submitting this set of guesses."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "sentence",
                                "text": "The resulting submission\u2014i.e., the maca- ronic sentence together with the set of guesses\u2014is logged in a database as a single training example, and the system displays feedback to the user about which guesses were correct."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
